  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the career options after diploma in electrical engineering?",
  "response": "After completing a diploma in electrical engineering, you have a variety of career options to choose from. Some of these career paths include:\n\n1. Electrical Technician: In this role, you would be responsible for installing, maintaining, and repairing electrical systems and equipment.\n\n2. Control Panel Designer: As a control panel designer, you would be responsible for designing and developing control panels for various industrial applications.\n\n3. Electrical Draftsman: As an electrical draftsman, you would be creating detailed technical drawings and plans for electrical systems and components.\n\n4. Field Service Technician: In this role, you would be responsible for installing, maintaining, and troubleshooting electrical equipment at customer sites.\n\n5. Maintenance Technician: As a maintenance technician, your primary responsibilities would include maintaining, troubleshooting, and repairing electrical systems and equipment.\n\n6. Electrical Estimator: In this role, you would be responsible for estimating the cost of electrical projects and preparing bids for contractors.\n\n7. Sales Engineer: As a sales engineer, you would be responsible for selling electrical equipment and systems, as well as providing technical support to customers.\n\n8. Project Manager: In this role, you would be overseeing and managing electrical projects, ensuring that they are completed on time and within budget.\n\n9. Quality Control Inspector: As a quality control inspector, you would be responsible for ensuring that electrical systems and components meet specified quality standards.\n\n10. Further education: You can also opt to pursue a bachelor's degree in electrical engineering or a related field, which would open up additional career opportunities, such as becoming a design engineer, research engineer, or a senior project manager.\n\nKeep in mind that these are just a few examples of career options available to you after completing a diploma in electrical engineering. With experience and further education, even more opportunities may become available to you.",
